value.value: An RNA molecule that is between 100 and 300 nucleotides in length and is present in the cytoplasm.
A DNA sequence within the host genome that is the target site of viral genome integration.

Refers to the hybridization of fluorescently labeled, chromosome-specific, composite probe pools to cytological preparations. It allows the visualization of individual chromosomes in metaphase or interphase cells and the identification of both numerical and structural chromosomal aberrations with high sensitivity and specificity.  Chromosome painting can be applied to cross-species comparisons as well as to the study of chromosomal rearrangements. The simultaneous hybridization of multiple chromosome painting probes, each tagged with a specific fluorochrome or fluorochrome combination, has resulted in the differential color display of chromosomes, i.e. spectral or color karyotyping. (From Ried et al 1998 Hum Mol Genet 7:1619)
The test system contains excess amount of binding agent.
An indication that the test system contains stimulating agent.
An indication that the test system does not contain stimulating agent.
An indication that the test system does not contain binding agent.
The arithmetic mean of a group of standardized (by total body weight) uptake values within a defined area or volume of interest (VOI).

label.value: Maximum Standardized Uptake Value Corrected for Lean Body Mass

value.value: The standardized uptake value corrected for lean body mass of the pixel or voxel with the strongest signal, within a defined area or volume of interest (VOI).

label.value: Mean Standardized Uptake Value Corrected for Lean Body Mass

value.value: The arithmetic mean of a group of standardized uptake values corrected for lean body mass within a defined area or volume of interest (VOI).

label.value: Peak Standardized Uptake Value Corrected for Lean Body Mass

value.value: The peak of standardized uptake value corrected for lean body mass distribution, generated by a histogram of all SUV values, across a defined area or volume of interest (VOI).
A test whose operational purpose is to determine the presence or absence of a substance, organism, or condition.
A test whose operational purpose is to verify the presence or absence of a substance, organism, or condition.

Single-pass reads of 200-800 bp that were obtained from randomly selected clones from cDNA libraries. They represent a snapshot of the genes expressed in a given tissue and/or at a given developmental stage for a given organism.
A test whose operational purpose is to determine the amount or concentration of a substance or organism.

label.value: Hundred Thousand Colony Forming Units per Milliliter

value.value: A unit of measurement of colony forming cells or microorganisms in a unit volume of substance of interest defined as the number of 10 to the fifth power colony forming units in one milliliter of substance.
A measurement from the top of the waist to the bottom of the heel.

A measurement of the length from the tip of the middle finger on one hand to the tip of the middle finger on the other hand with the individual standing against the wall with both arms abducted to 90 degrees, the elbows and wrists extended, and the palms facing directly forward. (Philip H. Quanjer, Andre Capderou, Mumtaz M. Mazicioglu, Ashutosh N. Aggarwal, Sudip Datta Banik, Stevo Popovic, Francis A.K. Tayie, Mohammad Golshan, Mary S.M. Ip, Marc Zelter. European Respiratory Journal 2014 44: 905-912)
The persistence of placental material after pregnancy.
The persistence of implantation site material after pregnancy.

label.value: Placental Remnant and Implantation Site Remnant

value.value: A finding that generally has features of placental remnants and implantation site remnants.
An increase in eosinophilic cytoplasmic droplets that appear glassy or translucent.
Testing activities involving clinical pathology for all endpoints within the study.
Testing activities involving clinical pathology for certain endpoints within the study.

an advantageous side-effect of a graft-vs-host reaction in which a leukemia patient is first irradiated to kill residual leukemic cells and is then given a bone marrow graft to replenish the immune system.  If cytotoxic T cells are not depleted from the bone marrow graft, these alloreactive T cells can attack the host's cells (graft-vs-host reaction) but can also attack the host's residual leukemic cells, thereby assisting in preventing recurrence of disease.
A laboratory procedure that involves the measurement of biotics and xenobiotics within a system.
Data analysis activities to characterize absorption, distribution, metabolism, and excretion (ADME) properties in relation to toxicity due to in vivo exposure to a substance/analyte.

label.value: Cervical Cancer by AJCC v9 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of cervical cancer according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer, 9th edition. This staging system applies to carcinomas and carcinosarcomas. It does not apply to sarcomas, lymphomas, and melanomas. Sarcomas are staged according to the corpus uteri classification for sarcomas. Lymphomas are staged according to Hodgkin and non-Hodgkin lymphoma classification. Melanomas are not staged. (from AJCC 9th Ed.)
A regimen consisting of lenalidomide and obinutuzumab that can be used in the treatment of some forms of non-Hodgkin's lymphoma (NHL).

label.value: Stage I Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

value.value: Stage I includes: T1, N0, M0. T1: Tumor strictly confined to the cervix (extension to corpus should be disregarded). N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 9th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IA Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

value.value: Stage IA includes: T1a, N0, M0. T1a: Tumor that can be diagnosed only by microscopy with maximum depth of invasion equal or less than 5 mm. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 9th Ed.)
A regimen consisting of dexamethasone and venetoclax that can be used for the treatment of relapsed or refractory plasma cell (multiple) myeloma.

label.value: Stage IA1 Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

value.value: Stage IA1 includes: T1a1, N0, M0. T1a1: Tumor with measured stromal invasion equal or less than 3 mm in depth. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 9th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IA2 Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

value.value: Stage IA2 includes: T1a2, N0, M0. T1a2: Tumor with measured stromal invasion of more than 3.0 mm and equal or less than 5.0 mm in depth. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 9th Ed.)
A regimen consisting of selinexor, dexamethasone and daratumumab that may be used for the treatment of relapsed or refractory plasma cell (multiple) myeloma.
Refers to the process by which students and teachers at different sites carry out learning and instruction via cable connection, conventional phone lines, or computer networks.

label.value: Stage IB Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

value.value: Stage IB includes: T1b, N0, M0. T1b: Tumor with measured deepest invasion more than 5 mm (greater than FIGO stage IA); lesion limited to the cervix uteri with size measured by maximum tumor diameter. Note: The involvement of vascular/lymphatic spaces should not change the staging. The lateral extent of the lesion is no longer considered. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 9th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IB1 Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

value.value: Stage IB1 includes: T1b1, N0, M0. T1b1: Tumor measuring more than 5 mm in depth and equal or less than 2 cm in greatest dimension. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 9th Ed.)

label.value: Auditory Brainstem Response Wave I, Absolute Latency

value.value: A measurement of the absolute latency of the auditory brainstem response wave I of the auditory evoked potential waveform.

label.value: Auditory Brainstem Response Wave V, Absolute Latency

value.value: A measurement of the absolute latency of the auditory brainstem response wave V of the auditory evoked potential waveform.

label.value: Auditory Brainstem Response Wave V, Amplitude

value.value: A measurement of the magnitude, or height, of the auditory brainstem response wave V of the auditory evoked potential waveform.

label.value: Auditory Brainstem Response Wave V, Presence

value.value: An assessment of the presence of the auditory brainstem response wave V of the auditory evoked potential waveform.

label.value: Stage IB2 Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

value.value: Stage IB2 includes: T1b2, N0, M0. T1b2: Tumor measuring more than 2 cm and equal or less than 4 cm in greatest dimension. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 9th Ed.)
A regimen consisting of bortezomib, cyclophosphamide, daratumumab and dexamethasone that can be used for the treatment of plasma cell (multiple) myeloma.
A regimen consisting of bortezomib, dexamethasone and selinexor that may be used for the treatment of relapsed or refractory plasma cell (multiple) myeloma.

label.value: Stage IB3 Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

value.value: Stage IB3 includes: T1b3, N0, M0. T1b3: Tumor measuring more than 4.0 cm in greatest dimension. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 9th Ed.)
An orderly array of DNA samples affixed to a support.  Using robots thousands of samples can be arrayed on a single chip. The chip is used in various types of hybridization experiments.
A regimen consisting of bortezomib, daratumumab, dexamethasone and lenalidomide that can be used for the treatment of plasma cell (multiple) myeloma.
A stage term referring to invasive cervical cancer that is confined to the cervix without lymph node involvement. It includes: T1b3, N0, M0. (partially adapted from AJCC)
A regimen consisting of bortezomib and lenalidomide that can be used for the treatment of plasma cell (multiple) myeloma.
